  "implementation_steps": [
    "1. Update `index.css` with the provided CSS variables for the 'Dark Swiss' theme.",
    "2. Install necessary packages: `lucide-react`, `framer-motion`, `sonner`, `clsx`, `tailwind-merge`.",
    "3. Create the `Layout` component with the Sidebar/Navbar structure.",
    "4. Implement the Authentication pages (Login/Register) using the `login_bg` image.",
    "5. Build the Dashboard shell using the 'Bento Grid' layout.",
    "6. Develop the 'User Management' and 'Task Management' modules using the customized Shadcn components.",
    "7. Apply `data-testid` to all interactive elements."
  ],
  "universal_guidelines": [
    "You tend to converge toward generic outputs. Avoid this.",
    "Dark colors look good when used independently without gradients. DO NOT use dark colors as gradients.",
    "Don't make generic centered layouts. Use grids.",
    "Create depth through layered design elements with z-index hierarchy.",
    "Use glass-morphism effects with backdrop filters (12-24px blur).",
    "You MUST NOT apply universal transition (e.g., `transition: all`).",
    "You MUST NOT center align the app container.",
    "Always use modern button styles (pill-shaped or sharp).",
    "Every interaction needs micro-animations.",
    "Use 2-3x more spacing than feels comfortable."
  ]
}